msgid "Parameters"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../Wrapping/Python/vtkmodules/numpy_interface/vtk_structured_point_array.py:157
msgid ""
"values : numpy array     The unique coordinate values for this axis. axis : "
"int     Which axis (0=X, 1=Y, 2=Z). dims : tuple of 3 ints     Grid "
"dimensions (nx, ny, nz). dataset : vtkDataObject, optional     The owning "
"dataset (kept as weak reference)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../Wrapping/Python/vtkmodules/numpy_interface/vtk_structured_point_array.py:207
msgid "Materialize the full 1D array using Fortran ordering (i fastest)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../Wrapping/Python/vtkmodules/numpy_interface/vtk_structured_point_array.py:215
msgid "Index into the array using Fortran ordering."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../Wrapping/Python/vtkmodules/numpy_interface/vtk_structured_point_array.py:223
msgid "Handle numpy ufuncs.  Unary ufuncs and scalar operations stay lazy."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../Wrapping/Python/vtkmodules/numpy_interface/vtk_structured_point_array.py:324
msgid ""
"When the direction matrix is identity (common case for vtkImageData and all "
"vtkRectilinearGrid), ufuncs and arithmetic operate per-axis and stay lazy.  "
"When a non-identity direction matrix is used, operations fall back to full "
"materialization."
msgstr ""

